greeting: Greetings from The On-Line Encyclopedia of Integer Sequences! http://oeis.org/

results.name: Array read by antidiagonals: T(n,k) is the number of non-isomorphic n X n nonnegative integer matrices with all row and column sums equal to k up to permutations of rows and columns.
comment: Terms may be computed without generating each matrix by enumerating the number of matrices by column sum sequence using dynamic programming. A PARI program showing this technique for the labeled case is given in A257493. Burnside's lemma can be used to extend this method to the unlabeled case.
results.author: _Andrew Howroyd_, Apr 04 2020
